name:                initwordlist
stack:               ( wid -- )
return stack:        ( -- )
string stack:        ( -- )
contexts:            stateless
category:            wordlists

decription:          declare/redeclare and empty the wordlist identified by wid.

example:             a sure way to trash all headers of forth vocabulary:
                     forth get-context initwordlist
                     (use   >exit    if you accidentally executed this)

standard:            I don't think so
deviation:           haven't checked yet
url:                 https://forth-standard.org/standard/core/INITWORDLIST
